Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 34-A MRSA ยง1210-E, sub-ยง2, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 732, Pt. A, ยง3
3 and affected by ยง5, is amended to read:
4 2. County Jail Operations Fund. The County Jail Operations Fund is established to
5 provide funding for county jails and the regional jail. State funding must be appropriated
6 annually for the fund in the an amount of $20,342,104 equal to 35% of the total cost of
7 operating the county jails and the regional jail as needed to meet the standards established
8 by the commissioner for county jails pursuant to sections 1208 and 1208-A, or otherwise
9 required by law, plus any additional amount the Legislature may appropriate. For purposes
10 of this section, the total cost of operating the county jails and the regional jail must reflect
11 the total cost of operating the county jails and the regional jail for the most recently
12 concluded fiscal year. The department shall administer the fund and shall distribute funds
13 to the jails in accordance with this section for the purposes set forth in subsections 3 and 4
14 and in accordance with the distribution formula set forth in subsection 9. County jails and
15 the regional jail may provide services that exceed the standards established pursuant to
16 sections 1208 and 1208-A or otherwise required by law, but the cost of providing such
17 services must be funded by the counties or from other sources outside of the fund.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This bill provides that state funding for the County Jail Operations Fund must be
2200 appropriated annually in an amount equal to 35% of the total cost of operations for county
2211 jails and the regional jail as necessary to meet the standards for county jails as established
2222 by the Commissioner of Corrections or otherwise required by law. The bill further provides
2233 that county jails and the regional jail may provide services that exceed the standards
2244 established by the commissioner or otherwise required by law, but the cost of providing
2255 such services must be funded by the counties or from other sources outside of the County
2266 Jail Operations Fund.
